  description="Explicit Agent is a minimalist Python framework for building agents whose logic, tool calls, and state are all visible by default."
  sections={[
    {
      heading: "The problem.",
      body: "Most agent frameworks optimize for elegance: a single decorator, hidden state, magic loops. That's great for demos and <strong>terrible for production</strong>. When something breaks at 2am, you want to read your code, not a stack trace through three libraries."
    },
    {
      heading: "The approach.",
      body: "Build the smallest possible framework where <strong>the agent loop is visible</strong>—no hidden orchestration, no implicit state, no surprising tool dispatch. Compose modular tools. Persist state explicitly. Swap models through LiteLLM or OpenRouter without rewriting the agent."
    },
    {
      heading: "The outcome.",
      body: "An open-source framework I use as the substrate for my own agent prototypes. Built on a simple hunch: in regulated or safety-critical contexts, <strong>transparency tends to age better than cleverness</strong>—because eventually someone has to answer 'why did the agent do that?'"
    }
  ]}
